#. [part]
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:91
msgid ""
"My control over the region was quickly asserted, and the peasants fell "
"quickly, if unhappily, back under the yoke. Despite their misgivings, the "
"festives were enjoyed by vampire and human alike. "
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:94
msgid ""
"The windsong did not take part, but rather worked without stop on excavating "
"the ruin. I had hatched several plans on how to aquire the prophesy after "
"the windsong had found it, but I knew that I had time to implement any of "
"them. My spies had informed me that the Windsong were making little headway, "
"and it would be months yet before they found what they were seeking."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:97
msgid ""
"The first month back in my lands was filled with battles. There were many "
"minor skirmishes with devlings, elementals, and even a pack of warg that "
"were infested with Rav Flu. These attacks did not dismay me, but only served "
"to stoke my curiosity as to the nature of the prophecy that the Windsong "
"were so desperately seeking. It would shed some light on the strange "
"behavior occurring throughout the region."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:100
msgid ""
"Four days into the second month, my thin bloods reported white banners in "
"the distance. I knew they were the banners of the Celestials, and at their "
"head would be their latest champion, Hezadin the Seer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Igor
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:120
msgid ""
"Mathter! The celethtials mean to thlay uth for good thith time. There are "
"even more of them than there wath when they conquered uth the firth time!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:124
#, fuzzy
msgid "There are so many... Summon Lisaundra."
msgstr "Ils sont si nombreux… Appelle Lisandra."

#. [message]: id=Igor
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:128
msgid "Here th'e comth."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Lisaundra
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:145
#, fuzzy
msgid "I still have not found it."
msgstr "Je ne l'ai toujours pas trouvé."

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:149
msgid "There are other matters that call our attention."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=prophet
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:153
msgid ""
"Lord Kromire, know that we will show no mercy, and that if you run, we will "
"only hunt you down. For the blood of seers and prophets runs in my veins, "
"and there is no place that you may hide from me. With the turmoil the world "
"is going through, we cannot afford to have a menace such as yourself on the "
"loose. This will be the final reckoning."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:157
msgid ""
"Blood of seers, you say, and prophets... Call your warriors out of that "
"hole, Lisaundra. Let us cease this slow search and fight. I must drink that "
"man's blood."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Lisaundra
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:161
msgid ""
"No, Kromire, I will not help you. I do not hate celestials, and have no love "
"for your kind. I am only here to accomplish my task, and then I will take my "
"leave. The celestials will not harm me, for they are intent on killing you, "
"and would not seek to offend the Windsong by drawing me into battle as well. "
"Fight your little battle by yourself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Igor
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:169
msgid "I would like to drink her blood..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:173
msgid ""
"It does not matter, once the blood of that prophet runs in my veins, we will "
"not need her. As much as I would like to punish her for her insolence, we "
"must let her be. As she said, now is not a good time to make enemies with "
"the Windsong."
msgstr ""

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:178
msgid "Kromire must hit Hazadin with his fangs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Valemoi
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:208
msgid ""
"Kromire, you were a fool to let me live. I have come to punish you for your "
"arrogance, pup. This time I will slay you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:212
#, fuzzy
msgid "Don't you have better things to be doing?"
msgstr "Vous n'avez rien de mieux à faire ?"

#. [message]: id=Valemoi
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:216
msgid ""
"NO! You left me broken and weak, and it took all I had to control my humans. "
"They rose up against me and drove me out, despite my power. I have nothing "
"left, and before I die, I will avenge myself!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:220
msgid ""
"Old fool. You are weak, and cannot truly think to kill me. Your desire for "
"vengeance is applaudable, but know that you do not stand a chance. I relish "
"the opportunity to slay you, as I should have done from the beginning."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:246
#, fuzzy
msgid ".... This is different..."
msgstr "… C'est différent …"

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:250
msgid "Such vision and insight, it burns in my veins more than magic..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:254
msgid ""
"Aha! Mwah-ha-ha! Come, Lisaundra, cease your silly search. I can tell you "
"the prophecy, it hangs in the air so heavy that I am surprised I could not "
"feel it before! Summon your scribe to witness and record the prophecy of "
"Mirrian the Ascendant."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Lisaundra
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:270
msgid ""
"I know not what you have wrought with this dark deed. This seems like "
"foolishness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:274
msgid ""
"Write these words down, it is not foolishness. This man's blood burned with "
"power, and all it took was my focus on the prophecy to draw it to the fore. "
"I can relate every line to you, or, if you doubt me, I can point you to "
"where the prophecy lies in the rubble."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Lisaundra
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:278
msgid "You do not lie... Esper, come quick. Write this down."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:293
msgid ""
"(Speaking as from a deep well) Behold, once the phoenix has flown, the Age "
"of the Unicorn is over. It is now the Age of the Dragon."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:297
msgid ""
"The events of the Age of the Dragon in order categorical are the War of the "
"Dragon, the Invasion from the Outlands, the Plague of the Dragon, and the "
"Empire of the Dragon. The age of the dragon ends when the north star turns "
"red."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:301
msgid ""
"The war of the dragon, will be the war between the Dark Dragon Kzardizin the "
"Immortal, and the inhabitants of the world. In the end either the dragon and "
"his minions will reign for the next two centuries, or the dragon will be "
"forced underground by three champions, one from the west, one from the "
"north, and one from the east."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:305
msgid ""
"The invasion from the outland will constitute of the rediscovery of the "
"gates to other worlds, and the interactions between the worlds. In the end "
"either the gates will be forbidden and lost, or they will be held open, but "
"guarded."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:309
msgid ""
"The plague of the dragon will be a vile illness that shall send the world "
"into chaos. In the end either four out of five of all animals and plants "
"will die, or an expedition into the Outland for the cure will be successful "
"and the afore stated ratio will be the number of survivors."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:313
msgid ""
"The Empire of the Dragon will be a new order forged out of the results of "
"the plague, and it will last several centuries. In the end it will either "
"fall to corruption caused by the renewal of necromancy, or it will be remade "
"from scratch, and renewed to face the next era, the Age of the Phoenix."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:317
msgid ""
"(Back to his ordinary voice) Know that this means that Kzardizin has "
"awakened, and that he will try to dominate the world. Return to the Great "
"Foundation, and tell your arbiters, ascendants, and librarians. Let them "
"know and prepare for the upcoming war. Kzardizin always had the loyalty of "
"devlings by promising them the chance to torment,   and the loyalty of many "
"vampires, by promising them blood. The many warriors of the dead were his "
"for he was a skilled necromancer, and also many warriors of the children of "
"his blood. Prepare your kind for this war,  as I shall seek to prepare mine. "
"I am the only vampire lord left in the northern part of these mountains, and "
"I will never submit to the rule of the Dark Dragon."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Lisaundra
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:321
msgid ""
"Nor will my people. This new age has much promise, but we must see that each "
"event has the proper ending."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kromire
#: Kromire/scenarios/9Prophecy.cfg:325
msgid ""
"I intend to live to the end. Through war and turmoil, through plague and "
"corruption, I will remain Count Kromire, Lord of the North Corian Mountains."
msgstr ""

